Package io.logspace.agent.api.event

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Event
    The Event is the core part of the logspace domain: they must have a globally unique identifier, they must have a timestamp they can have a type, they can reference other Events a global Event which is the root cause for other Events a parent Event which is the direct predecessor Event and the can carry any additional information in the form of a collection of key-value pairs.
    EventProperty<T>
    The interface defining a property of an Event.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractEventBuilder
    Base class for Event Builders.
    AbstractEventProperty<T>
    Abstract base class for implementing an EventProperty allowing type-safe property values using generics.
    BooleanEventProperty
    An EventProperty carrying a Boolean as value.
    DateEventProperty
    An EventProperty carrying a Date as value.
    DefaultEventBuilder
    Default implementation of an event builder which sets an empty type.
    DoubleEventProperty
    An EventProperty carrying a Double as value.
    EventBuilderData
    Contains the basic information required for creating a new Event Builder.
    EventProperties
    A collection of EventProperties.
    FloatEventProperty
    An EventProperty carrying a Float as value.
    ImmutableEvent
    Immutable Event implementation.
    IntegerEventProperty
    An EventProperty carrying a Integer as value.
    LongEventProperty
    An EventProperty carrying a Long as value.
    StringEventProperty
    An EventProperty carrying a String as value.
